verses.roman:
pāche more prasāda govinda dibe bahirdvāre
mana jāni' prabhu punaḥ nā balila tāṅre

synonyms: pāche—at last; more—unto me; prasāda—remnants of food; govinda—the personal servant of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; dibe—will deliver; bahir-dvāre—outside the door; mana jāni'—understanding the mind; prabhu—Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; punaḥ—again; nā—not; balila—called; tāṅre—him.
translation: "Govinda will give me prasāda later, outside the door." Understanding his mind, Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu did not call him again.
